The widow of slain drug baron Ibrahim Akasha has denied her two extradited sons were involved in drug trafficking. On Thursday, Fatuma said her children do honest businesses and depend on their father&rsquo;s wealth. &ldquo;My husband was involved in car importation and selling jewellery. He was a big supplier of gold,&rdquo;she said. Fatuma said her sons shouldn&rsquo;t have been extradited.